Author: BVeyron
Title: [ANN] Bowhead Health: Personalized Health Platform
Body: The question to devs of this project: do you realize that the actual importance of medical information is not as high people think? The actual problem of medicine is NOT the lack of data about patients - the archives of reliant information about previous diseases is what every, for example, elderly, or disabled person has, and he or she stores it, and brings it at every healthcare procedure. The actual problem of medicine is that people simply do not want to concern about their health and ignore doctors' advices, neither patients nor doctors need all those tons of samples or investigation results at all - both are just dealing with the current acute case, and as for the further treatment - serious health problems are never being ignored by patients, and they would always have the precise information about such cases, and as for simple cases - no need to store the full archive of the case, anyway nobody will follow the doctor's advice

Author: @fdiazmitoma
Title: [ANN] Bowhead Health: Personalized Health Platform
Body: Hello NewWorldCoiner,  Please see my paper: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC497566/pdf/0023-04.pdf; we have experience with the development of these tests. Our partners are the leading developer of lateral flow tests in Southern California. The lateral flow diagnostic technology has evolved substantially in the last 10 years. We are targeting technical improvements like this:https://www.nature.com/articles/srep28645.pdf and also this: http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article/file?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0156866&type=printable. Bowhead Health is not similar to Theranos. We have a different approach to diagnostics as described above and also our business model creates value not only from accurate diagnostics but from the capacity to dispense supplements and medications in a personalized manner.  If you like to see our patent application. Please provide a name, address and a confidentiality agreements and we will send submission. The patent application supports the use of a diagnostic and a dispensing device and Bowhead Health business model as described above. We are a startup with a working prototype, a group of experts in diagnostics, medical informatics, robotics and manufacturing. The business is a work in progress, including the integration of blockchain medical informatics, diagnostics and personalized dispensing of required supplements.  There are several companies with diagnostics for malaria, but that is not our proposed core business.  There will be bugs and problems with our device and we are identifying those now. We will also have a  market beta test to identify other issues that we may not be aware at this point in time.

Body: No proof then? Author: NewWorldCoiner
Title: [ANN] Bowhead Health: Personalized Health Platform
Body: Ok, I'll bite, seeing as you want to play. You send me to the top google result for computer vision - is that because you can't explain it yourself, much like Theranos couldn't explain how their machine worked?  Your proof of patent seems to be a quote from your whitepaper - well that's no proof at all. What are the filing numbers? The USPTO has no results for Bowhead Health, just a couple about aboriginal quotas for bowhead whales. https://search.uspto.gov/search?query=bowhead&op=Search&affiliate=web-sdmg-uspto.gov  It was claimed in the video that this is not a ripoff of another product - but this company has a working device for malaria. http://www.sightdx.com/infectious-diseases/parasight/  Finally, you ignore the problems associated with what you claim your machine is capable of - is that because you don't know what those problems are, or that you do know, but are choosing not to mention them because you want a fat ICO? Where is your peer reviewed evidence to show that this technique of small volume sampling is accurate and reliable?  If you can square all that away, then we can talk about getting computer vision to determine the correct reagent strength, something Theranos couldn't do, despite their 8 pages of patents covering most aspects of this kind of test.

Body: New thread: https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2047429.0 Bowhead Health Personalized Health Platform   WEBSITE | WHITEPAPER｜TWITTER｜REDDIT｜FACEBOOK｜SLACK｜TELEGRAM ICO LAUNCH - 17th July 2017   Official Bounty Campaign  Russian  - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2006378 Italian - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=1999705.0 Polish - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=1999919 Filipino - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=1997166.0 Indonesian - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=1997122 Hindi - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2005091.0 French  - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2005791.0 Chinese  - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2004629.0 Turkish  - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2023361 Dutch  - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2014489 Greek - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2012774.0 Portuguese - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2011531 Spanish - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2016756 German - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2019232 Bulgarian - https://bitcoinbg.eu/forum/viewtopic.php?f=20&t=4477&p=43712#p43712  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tpUzs4wivYU  Abstract    The world’s healthcare is broken and needs to be fixed. Per the World Bank, global spending on health is expected to increase to $18.28 trillion. Despite this, many people are still not healthy or happy. Many developing nations do not even have the most basic of healthcare services and technology. Generic drugs, which are cost effective, do not reach people who need them most. However, times are changing. Leaps are being made in digital health technology and prevention, and generally speaking, human lifespan is increasing. Remote at-home testing and diagnostic devices are seeing rapid advances and will revolutionize convenient and accessible healthcare at home.  We believe that lack of access to convenient personal healthcare services is a barrier to humans around the world, keeping them from having longer, healthier and happier lives. Beyond these challenges are opportunities. We are in a stage where large incumbent healthcare, technology and pharmaceutical companies are vying to compete to control patients’ data in a centralized system for their own benefit. Naturally, this reduces the portability of data for patients and further embeds the incumbents and their grip on a patients’ data. The future requires a decentralized Blockchain-based repository controlled by the patient to ensure maximum security and portability. Blockchain is a perfectly suited transparent system where patients can use Bowhead Tokens to pay for healthcare practitioners, medicine, and nutritional supplements. Patients will also receive Bowhead tokens for participating in healthier activities to incentivize preventive health.  Bowhead believes personalized and secure healthcare is possible for everyone.   Bowhead platform   For the past 18 months we have developed working prototypes of the following:   Bowhead is an instrument that is connected to the internet and can monitor the health of individuals at home and can also be a resource of information for healthcare professionals to provide timely advice to people in need of health attention and direction. The instrument can dispense personalized medication and nutritional supplements based on the unique needs of a customer.   How it works   1.User provides a blood prick (similar to glucose test) or saliva sample 2.User inserts cartridge into the side of the device 3.Bowhead device uses computer vision to determine reagent strength and signal 4.Based on reading: licensed doctor offers recommendation and dispensing occurs 5.All signals monitored securely and stored using Blockchain technology    Blockchain database    By using Blockchain, health records can be perfectly interoperable across different organizations, all the while being secure and reconciled to be the most up to date.  Blockchain is being successfully used to manage healthcare records in Estonia.  Bowhead will use a similar model with a patent-pending Bowhead innovation called Anonymized Healthcare Token which uses smart contracts to produce this enforceable flow:  1. Research institutions or pharmaceutical companies can create profiles of attributes they are looking to research and offer a leasing bounty 2. The decentralized system will have an intermittent function where anonymized patient records or monitored and compared against the research attributes of the research institution. 3. Patients will have the option to participate 4. Patients will have the option to view the leasing offer for anonymized patient data and any additional characteristics of the study 5. If a patient agrees, they will have full control on what is leased using a smart contract. Typically we envision patients not sharing things like their full name, address or personal identifiable information.    Using health data to fuel crypto economics   We believe patient data is some of the most valuable data in the world, Bowhead will use anonymized patient data to add value while ensuring data is protected using cryptography. For example, every new patient that is completes a health-focused survey or completes a diagnostic test may have the option to receive Bowhead tokens.     Market and industry   Per Deloitte’s 2017 report, the global healthcare market is predicted to reach $8.7 Trillion USD by 2020.  Within the global medical technology segment here are the sales:   The following graph compares the total venture funding in each Health Technology category to the number of companies in the category. The Digital Medical Devices category leads in both metrics, with around $8funding and about 225 startups.
